00:47.757 --> 00:54.722
♪ And you'll drown
Before the water lets you in ♪♪

01:21.833 --> 01:23.835
[♪♪♪]

01:27.839 --> 01:30.215
[Potts on recording]
Date is November 11th, 1983.

01:30.424 --> 01:32.593
Interview with John Rayburn.

01:33.011 --> 01:34.846
And what happened?

01:35.847 --> 01:37.849
He was hit by a car.

01:41.143 --> 01:43.354
[Potts]
So then you helped him up.

01:43.688 --> 01:45.731
Brought him inside the house?

01:46.732 --> 01:48.567
[young John]
Yes, sir.

01:49.652 --> 01:51.236
[Potts]
Okay.

01:51.779 --> 01:54.073
Will you send in your brother?

01:59.871 --> 02:01.413
[young Kevin]
I'm Kevin.

02:01.914 --> 02:03.624
Kevin Rayburn.

02:04.500 --> 02:06.836
[Potts]
You saw the car hit your brother?

02:07.419 --> 02:08.880
[Kevin]
Yes, sir.

02:09.505 --> 02:12.174
Danny was screaming and crying.

02:14.552 --> 02:16.929
I never saw someone get hurt that bad.

02:22.518 --> 02:24.520
[♪♪♪]

03:08.147 --> 03:09.774
Mama.

03:10.149 --> 03:12.610
[Diana]
So you lied to the police.

03:12.860 --> 03:14.445
Yeah.

03:14.904 --> 03:17.740
That was 30 years ago.
How old were you, 14?

03:18.741 --> 03:20.785
I still knew it was wrong.

03:24.455 --> 03:26.749
All these years,
you guys never spoke about it?

03:27.083 --> 03:28.876
Not till yesterday.

03:31.003 --> 03:32.337
How did that go?

03:33.089 --> 03:34.173
I apologized.

03:36.008 --> 03:37.051
And?

03:37.802 --> 03:40.262
I think he was all right with it.

03:44.058 --> 03:45.309
What?

03:48.771 --> 03:51.732
It could have just as easily
been me on that boat with Sarah.

03:59.573 --> 04:03.368
I'm glad that you guys finally
had a chance to talk about this.

04:13.212 --> 04:14.922
I feel like things can be better now.

04:18.258 --> 04:20.970
Just don't expect too much, you know?

04:21.137 --> 04:22.805
People don't change overnight.

04:26.266 --> 04:27.977
There's...

04:28.644 --> 04:30.813
- Let me get that for you.
- Looks scrumptious.

04:30.980 --> 04:33.357
- Oh, thank you.
- Of course.

04:33.440 --> 04:34.859
Oh...

04:42.033 --> 04:45.577
You've made a real commitment
here, Danny. I'm proud of you.

04:47.705 --> 04:48.956
Mm.

04:50.415 --> 04:52.877
I talked to Gwen about a raise.

04:53.418 --> 04:55.129
Yeah.

04:58.674 --> 05:00.801
Oh. Thanks, Mom.

05:01.010 --> 05:02.344
This'll be a big help.

05:27.828 --> 05:29.163
[engine starts]

05:32.917 --> 05:34.919
[cell phone buzzing]

05:42.260 --> 05:44.095
[buzzing continues]

05:54.563 --> 05:56.356
Oh, shit.

06:05.283 --> 06:06.909
Where are we?

06:08.202 --> 06:09.870
A boat.

06:10.495 --> 06:12.248
- Yours?
- No.

06:12.456 --> 06:14.125
Not exactly.

06:18.003 --> 06:19.504
[door opens]

06:33.185 --> 06:35.187
[birds squawking]

06:46.324 --> 06:50.202
[Danny] I'm getting paid shit at the inn.
Absolute shit.

06:51.411 --> 06:54.123
You know, I gotta make more cash.

06:54.332 --> 06:56.083
The old man didn't
leave you anything?

06:56.292 --> 06:57.793
[Danny]
No.

06:58.043 --> 06:59.253
He cut me out of his will.

06:59.419 --> 07:01.546
Of course he fucking did.

07:02.381 --> 07:04.967
He offered me a chunk
of change to leave, though.

07:05.176 --> 07:06.218
Why didn't you take it?

07:06.385 --> 07:08.428
Because he fucking died
before I had a chance.

07:08.512 --> 07:10.097
Oh. Fuck him.

07:10.306 --> 07:11.890
Anyway...

07:12.724 --> 07:14.185
I wanna stay here.

07:14.393 --> 07:16.812
I wanna fucking get what's mine.

07:17.021 --> 07:19.148
Do what I gotta do.

07:21.859 --> 07:23.902
But I'm in the hole fucking bad.

07:24.111 --> 07:25.404
And this shit?

07:25.612 --> 07:26.905
It's just not gonna cut it.

07:27.114 --> 07:29.950
This shit's the best I can offer you, pal.

07:31.618 --> 07:32.995
Hey.

07:33.453 --> 07:35.873
Let me talk to your guy.

07:36.081 --> 07:37.833
No fucking way.

07:38.042 --> 07:40.002
No. They want us
to keep quiet, do our job.

07:40.085 --> 07:43.214
- Exactly what we're gonna do.
- Eric, there's an opportunity here.

07:43.381 --> 07:46.925
- Something at the end of those gas cans.
- We got a good thing here.

07:47.301 --> 07:49.761
Look at what we got.
We got-- It's quiet.

07:49.970 --> 07:53.015
It's simple, it's safe. I'm not
gonna do anything to fuck that up.

07:58.562 --> 08:00.356
All right, thanks, Chase. Bye.

08:00.731 --> 08:02.983
Marathon P.D. just called
with a heads-up.

08:03.192 --> 08:04.985
DA's setting up surveillance
in Tom's Harbor.

08:05.194 --> 08:07.405
- The marina?
- Yep. They think it's narcotics.

08:07.487 --> 08:10.324
They promised to keep us in the loop.
We'll see. What's that?

08:10.532 --> 08:13.035
That trafficking ring
that brought in Cristina Colon?

08:13.202 --> 08:15.746
Five men were convicted.
Five were serving time,

08:15.954 --> 08:17.206
Miami federal prison.

08:17.581 --> 08:18.790
There's Miami.

08:18.999 --> 08:20.500
Pensacola.

08:20.709 --> 08:24.296
This one was killed by another inmate
in Tallahassee in a labor camp.

08:24.504 --> 08:25.756
This is Ray Jenkins.

08:25.964 --> 08:27.716
Ray got himself an early release.

08:27.925 --> 08:30.094
I imagine you wanna go talk to him, huh?

08:30.761 --> 08:34.181
If you're hungry, why don't you grab
a donut? I'm not stopping on the way.

08:40.104 --> 08:41.563
[Kevin clears throat]

08:43.899 --> 08:45.650
Some night, huh?

08:47.278 --> 08:49.947
- Thanks for the ride.
- No problem.

08:54.076 --> 08:55.494
[truck door closes]

08:57.246 --> 08:59.581
I was thinking we could just
keep this between us.

08:59.790 --> 09:01.833
I could not agree more.

09:05.463 --> 09:07.298
[engine starts]

09:16.515 --> 09:18.934
Mr. Davis, were you in
the bar when the fight began?

09:19.143 --> 09:21.979
Yeah. I was coming out the john.

09:22.187 --> 09:24.356
How many drinks
do you think you had?

09:24.440 --> 09:26.191
Objection. Relevance.

09:26.400 --> 09:28.819
Mr. Davis claims to have
witnessed the altercation.

09:29.027 --> 09:31.780
I think it's very important,
the state of his sobriety.

09:32.656 --> 09:33.698
You can answer.

09:34.574 --> 09:37.161
I don't know,
probably six or seven beers.

09:37.453 --> 09:39.871
What did you see when you
came out of the restroom?

09:40.705 --> 09:43.959
The Mexican guy grabbed the victim,
threw him down and pulled a knife.

09:44.251 --> 09:45.377
Mr. Mejia's Cuban.

09:46.337 --> 09:49.548
But you're saying that you saw
Mr. Mejia draw a weapon.

09:50.007 --> 09:51.675
- Clear as day.
- Okay.

09:51.883 --> 09:55.220
Well, then, I'm just wondering
what hand he might have had a knife in.

09:55.971 --> 09:57.931
Uh...

09:58.015 --> 09:59.099
His right hand.

10:01.393 --> 10:02.436
And then?

10:02.894 --> 10:05.647
Then he said he wanted his money,
or he'd cut up the victim.

10:05.856 --> 10:07.774
So the victim gave him what he had.

10:08.233 --> 10:10.528
Did you see Mr. Mejia use the knife?

10:10.735 --> 10:12.488
No, he just grabbed the cash and ran.

10:12.696 --> 10:15.282
- And you called the police.
- Yeah.

10:15.949 --> 10:17.451
Is the victim a friend of yours?

10:17.951 --> 10:19.870
No. I just felt bad for the guy.

10:21.246 --> 10:22.914
Your phone records
from that night

10:22.998 --> 10:25.250
show that you made
another call as well.

10:26.502 --> 10:28.628
- Yeah, I did.
- Who'd you call?

10:30.255 --> 10:32.383
Um... Uh...

10:32.466 --> 10:35.719
- The victim's sister.
- Oh, did the victim give you her number?

10:35.927 --> 10:37.388
No.

10:38.096 --> 10:41.225
Then how exactly did you know
where to reach her?

10:50.234 --> 10:53.195
[Eric]
What the fuck was that all about?

10:54.196 --> 10:56.281
Is it really your business?

10:57.199 --> 10:59.743
Did you spend the night
with that asshole?

11:01.620 --> 11:03.247
[Chelsea]
What do you care?

11:03.455 --> 11:05.541
Well, I care, because
Captain Fucking Rayburn

11:05.707 --> 11:08.710
is the douchiest shit bag
in that whole fucking family.

11:11.255 --> 11:12.672
You did.

11:13.673 --> 11:15.675
Well, that's good. That's good.

11:15.842 --> 11:17.928
- What are you gonna tell Danny?
- Nothing.

11:18.136 --> 11:19.179
Nothing?

11:19.388 --> 11:21.098
No, he's not gonna find out, right?

11:21.306 --> 11:22.641
I don't care if he finds out.

11:22.849 --> 11:25.269
That's my best friend
we're talking about, you know?

11:25.477 --> 11:28.439
Your best friend made it clear that
he wants nothing to do with me.

11:28.855 --> 11:31.691
So save your fucking
lectures for someone else.

11:32.651 --> 11:34.986
Why don't you start looking
for your own place, too?

11:35.070 --> 11:36.405
[door slams]

11:39.699 --> 11:42.077
Certainly is a prime piece of waterfront.

11:42.286 --> 11:44.580
Yeah. Could more than double
my business.

11:44.788 --> 11:47.832
You'd have to make improvements
on the existing structure.

11:48.041 --> 11:49.126
That won't be cheap.

11:49.334 --> 11:53.046
Yeah, but see, I thought I could use
the loan for that as well, right?

11:53.255 --> 11:56.467
And then, I'll use my place as collateral.

11:57.551 --> 11:59.595
The bank will need
to assess your property

11:59.803 --> 12:01.972
and the business before
I can give my approval.

12:02.180 --> 12:04.433
Sure thing. Take a look around.
She's all yours.

12:04.642 --> 12:06.768
- You know, kick the tires, whatever.
- [laughs]

12:06.977 --> 12:09.271
I can't do it all today. It's a process.

12:09.480 --> 12:12.149
- You're from around here?
- Born and raised in Big Pine.

12:12.316 --> 12:14.151
I knew it. I knew it. I can tell.

12:14.359 --> 12:16.945
- A thousand miles away. Conch pride.
- Mm.

12:17.154 --> 12:19.156
Listen, this is really important to me.

12:19.364 --> 12:21.032
You know?
This isn't just a business.

12:21.241 --> 12:22.867
It's a local place for local folks,

12:23.034 --> 12:26.246
and I'm really trying to keep it that way.

12:26.330 --> 12:28.123
I've put my whole life
into this place

12:28.206 --> 12:29.791
- because I care.
- I can see that.

12:29.874 --> 12:32.711
Those other guys who wanna
buy that property, they don't care.

12:33.920 --> 12:35.589
I'll send out the assessor,

12:35.714 --> 12:37.716
- and we'll get things rolling.
- Fantastic.

12:38.133 --> 12:39.759
Thank you. My sister's an attorney.

12:39.843 --> 12:42.387
She's gonna help me get
my financials all together.

12:42.471 --> 12:43.805
- Her name's Meg.
- Mm-hm.

12:43.972 --> 12:46.684
- Okay. I'll be in touch.
- All right. Take care, Debbie.

12:46.766 --> 12:48.727
- Bye.
- Bye.

12:52.397 --> 12:54.024
[engine starts]

12:56.067 --> 12:58.111
[woman speaking on TV, indistinct]

13:08.997 --> 13:12.501
Monroe County Police Department.
Ray Jenkins, open up.

13:21.760 --> 13:23.803
Ray, open up now.

13:25.930 --> 13:28.433
- The fuck is this about?
- Hi, I'm Detective Rayburn.

13:28.517 --> 13:30.477
- This is Detective Diaz.
- Can we come in?

13:30.686 --> 13:33.188
On a beautiful day like today?

13:33.397 --> 13:34.732
I think fucking not.

13:34.981 --> 13:37.568
Ma'am. You're gonna wanna
step back inside, please.

13:37.859 --> 13:39.194
- Thank you, ma'am.
- [John] Ray.

13:41.279 --> 13:42.906
Are you still trafficking girls?

13:45.825 --> 13:47.745
Who's running the women these days,
Ray?

13:47.952 --> 13:51.415
Why don't you listen to WKWT?
You get your traffic on the ones.

13:55.335 --> 13:56.836
[John]
Listen to me, you asshole.

13:56.920 --> 13:59.297
I don't know who you fucked
over to get out of jail,

13:59.381 --> 14:01.800
but I'll end your fucking
probation now. Understand?

14:02.342 --> 14:04.511
You got a weapon in there?
I'll send you back.

14:04.720 --> 14:07.264
You got weed in there,
I'll fucking send you back.

14:07.389 --> 14:09.349
- Do you understand me?
- Jesus fuck--

14:09.558 --> 14:12.811
Ray. These girls were killed
on their way into the country.

14:13.019 --> 14:14.104
Recognize them?

14:16.064 --> 14:17.941
- You recognize them?
- I'm out of that.

14:18.024 --> 14:20.694
My crew's still in prison.
I ain't planning on going back.

14:20.778 --> 14:21.986
[Marco]
Anybody recruit you

14:22.070 --> 14:23.154
- when you got out?
- No.

14:23.363 --> 14:25.365
Who took over after
your ring was busted up?

14:25.574 --> 14:28.076
I'm sure someone did, but they ain't
come knock on my door.

14:28.159 --> 14:29.745
[John]
Don't raise your voice, Ray.

14:29.911 --> 14:31.079
Why don't you try a farm?

14:32.038 --> 14:34.082
Farm-- You know,
this attitude that you got,

14:34.291 --> 14:36.042
- it's not helping--
- No, farm.

14:36.251 --> 14:37.544
Fucking orchards.

14:37.753 --> 14:39.921
You know, fruits and guavas
and shit like that.

14:40.130 --> 14:41.923
They always need spics over there.

14:42.299 --> 14:43.759
Spic?

14:44.301 --> 14:46.177
No offense.

14:46.511 --> 14:48.847
That's the least offensive
thing about you, Ray.

14:49.848 --> 14:53.101
- Most of them hire illegals.
- Who's the biggest fucking employer?

14:54.018 --> 14:55.604
We brought them to five or six.

14:55.813 --> 14:57.981
I asked you who's the biggest one, Ray.

14:58.189 --> 15:00.233
Bezler, I guess.

15:00.734 --> 15:03.278
Bezler Farms. Bezler Orchards.

15:03.361 --> 15:05.656
You ever end up torching
one of your own boats?

15:05.739 --> 15:07.157
- No. Never.
- [John] No?

15:07.365 --> 15:09.993
- You sure?
- Look, I gave you what you want.

15:10.619 --> 15:12.454
We're square, yeah?

15:14.205 --> 15:17.668
Yeah, sure, Ray. You're an upstanding
citizen, and we appreciate you.

15:18.585 --> 15:20.044
Adios.

15:26.426 --> 15:29.429
Tell his parole officer
he's been smoking dope.

15:32.307 --> 15:33.350
You're serious?

15:34.058 --> 15:35.686
Fuck him.

15:37.061 --> 15:39.063
[rock ballad playing over speakers]

15:47.698 --> 15:49.073
Couple more gigs like this,

15:49.157 --> 15:52.911
and I can move out of
my fucking sister's place. Here.

15:53.411 --> 15:55.079
Yeah. It's a start.

15:55.288 --> 15:56.707
Alabama eight-ball.

15:56.915 --> 15:58.124
Fifty bucks a pop.

15:58.333 --> 15:59.835
You rack, I break.

16:00.043 --> 16:01.920
- No, man. Not today, bro.
- Come on.

16:02.128 --> 16:04.130
- No. Gotta go.
- Stick around, would you?

16:04.339 --> 16:05.465
I gotta go.

16:07.050 --> 16:08.218
You want a beer? A drink?

16:08.426 --> 16:10.345
- What is it?
- Wine? Sangria? Something?

16:10.512 --> 16:11.555
What? What? What?

16:11.763 --> 16:14.224
My fucking sister didn't
come home last night.

16:15.809 --> 16:18.520
Okay. It's not my business.

16:20.564 --> 16:21.648
Okay.

16:21.773 --> 16:23.983
All right. Great, go.
Fucking have a great day.

16:24.067 --> 16:25.527
- None of your business.
- Okay.

16:25.610 --> 16:28.906
Good. So you don't give a shit
that Kevin dropped her off, right?

16:29.113 --> 16:30.156
Kevin who?

16:30.615 --> 16:32.743
Kevin. Your fucking brother.

16:33.451 --> 16:37.038
That Kevin. Now, you want me to fucking
teach him some fucking respect,

16:37.247 --> 16:39.499
you just give me the word,
I'll fucking do it.

16:39.708 --> 16:42.126
No. No, no, no. Don't-- It's all right.

16:42.335 --> 16:43.420
It's not all right.

16:43.545 --> 16:45.213
- Their busin--
- It's not all right.

16:45.422 --> 16:47.925
They're both adults, man.
Don't worry about it.

16:48.132 --> 16:49.426
[scoffs]

16:49.676 --> 16:51.845
You're a fucking piece of work, dude.

16:52.053 --> 16:54.013
This fucking little prick disrespects you,

16:54.222 --> 16:56.391
and you're just like, "Oh, yeah."

16:56.600 --> 16:58.685
You know what?
Kevin can do whatever he wants.

16:59.060 --> 17:02.230
I got bigger things to worry about, man.

17:02.814 --> 17:04.691
[♪♪♪]

17:04.775 --> 17:07.068
♪ My veins are blue and connected ♪

17:07.193 --> 17:09.988
♪ And every single bone in my brain
Is electric ♪

17:10.071 --> 17:12.574
♪ But I dig ditches
Like the best of 'em ♪

17:24.669 --> 17:28.339
♪ And even God herself
Has fewer plans than me ♪

17:28.423 --> 17:31.301
♪ But she never helps me out
With my scams for free though ♪

17:31.426 --> 17:33.720
♪ She grabs a stick
And then she points it at me ♪

17:33.845 --> 17:36.807
♪ When I say nothing
I say everything ♪

17:37.557 --> 17:42.103
♪ Yeah, when I say nothing
I say everything ♪

17:42.186 --> 17:47.525
♪ They threw me down in the lazaretto
Born rottin', bored rotten ♪

17:47.651 --> 17:52.823
♪ Makin' models of people I used to know
Out of coffee and cotton ♪

17:52.906 --> 17:55.533
♪ And all my illegitimate kids
Have begotten ♪

17:55.617 --> 17:58.495
♪ Thrown down to the wolves
Made feral for nothin' ♪

17:58.620 --> 18:00.413
♪ Quarantine on the Isle of Man ♪

18:00.538 --> 18:04.042
♪ And I'm trying to escape
Any way that I can, oh ♪

18:04.125 --> 18:06.670
♪ Any way that I can, oh ♪

18:08.964 --> 18:10.632
♪ I have no time left ♪

18:10.757 --> 18:14.260
♪ Time is lost, no time at all
Throw it in a garbage can ♪

18:14.344 --> 18:17.180
♪ And I shake God's hand
I jump up ♪

18:17.305 --> 18:20.141
♪ And let her know when I can
This is how we're gonna do it ♪♪

18:51.506 --> 18:53.508
[♪♪♪]

19:21.536 --> 19:26.165
[all laughing]

19:26.332 --> 19:29.794
But when your dad decided
that he was gonna get your mom...

19:31.004 --> 19:32.463
no matter what,

19:32.672 --> 19:35.425
he pulled out all the stops.

19:35.633 --> 19:37.928
You know, I'm talking
about a full-court press.

19:38.136 --> 19:40.471
- That's my Mr. Smooth.
- [Danny] Full-court press.

19:40.555 --> 19:42.557
And so she had tickets

19:42.766 --> 19:44.935
to a concert in Miami.

19:45.143 --> 19:47.520
[Diana]
Oh, that's right. Who was that?

19:47.729 --> 19:49.439
- Pet Shop Boys.
- [Danny] Yeah.

19:49.647 --> 19:52.567
- Pet Shop Boys, it was indeed.
- [Diana laughs]

19:52.650 --> 19:55.112
And your dad decided
he had to have a new shirt.

19:55.319 --> 19:57.906
He had to have a new shirt
for the occasion.

19:58.115 --> 19:59.365
He wanted something

19:59.574 --> 20:01.701
that looked nicer
than what he usually wears.

20:01.910 --> 20:02.953
Which wouldn't be hard.

20:03.327 --> 20:06.081
I have no idea what these
two are talking about.

20:06.289 --> 20:08.249
So, he had no money,

20:08.458 --> 20:10.752
because he spent
all his money on his new engine.

20:10.961 --> 20:13.130
Blah, blah. He wasn't gonna
ask our dad for money,

20:13.337 --> 20:15.339
so he starts asking me

20:15.548 --> 20:17.050
for some shoplifting tips.

20:17.258 --> 20:19.177
- No way. What?
- No, that never happened.

20:19.385 --> 20:24.015
- I never stole a thing in my life.
- Oh, I think that's not entirely true.

20:24.223 --> 20:27.018
Well, that's kind of romantic,
stealing for your woman.

20:27.226 --> 20:29.062
- Should've told me.
- It did not happen.

20:29.146 --> 20:31.064
I look like a guy who cares
about clothes?

20:31.272 --> 20:32.649
- [Danny] Oh, boy.
- [John] You sure, son?

20:32.732 --> 20:34.192
- [Janey] You should.
- Oh, boy.

20:34.275 --> 20:36.319
But you wanted to impress this lady.

20:36.527 --> 20:38.196
That much might be true.

20:39.489 --> 20:40.907
[Danny] But anyway.

20:41.116 --> 20:43.367
He didn't have to, you know.

20:43.576 --> 20:47.205
He didn't have to steal anything,
because I stole it for him.

20:50.041 --> 20:51.126
How was the concert?

20:52.210 --> 20:55.588
I think that's the first
night they, uh, kissed.

20:55.839 --> 20:57.715
- [Diana] Um...
- I remember that night.

20:58.049 --> 20:59.843
Yeah, I remember that shirt.

21:00.510 --> 21:02.595
[all chuckle]

21:05.140 --> 21:07.892
This is all you need, right here.

21:08.101 --> 21:10.478
Patch of breeze,
a patch of water,

21:10.687 --> 21:12.814
a beautiful-- Oh, look. Oh.

21:16.776 --> 21:18.945
Who does this fucking guy
think he is, huh?

21:19.154 --> 21:20.404
- Pulling up here--
- Night.

21:20.989 --> 21:22.157
[Diana]
Janey.

21:22.532 --> 21:25.243
Honey, wait up. You forget your cell.

21:25.451 --> 21:26.828
We talked about this.

21:27.037 --> 21:28.579
[Janey]
Thanks.

21:29.122 --> 21:30.540
You have a good time.

21:30.748 --> 21:34.878
Hey, Janey, this guy's a teenager.
You gotta keep him off balance.

21:35.378 --> 21:37.296
I've got a few tricks.

21:37.588 --> 21:39.507
Yeah-- Hey. Don't give him

21:39.716 --> 21:41.509
what he wants at the end of the night.

21:41.718 --> 21:44.345
- Eleven o'clock. No later.
- Got it.

21:44.554 --> 21:46.014
[Danny]
Janey. Janey.

21:47.140 --> 21:48.432
Janey, come here.

21:48.892 --> 21:50.977
Come here. I wanna tell you something.

21:58.651 --> 22:02.488
[whispering]
Where the parts go...

22:03.364 --> 22:05.783
If you like this guy...

22:06.951 --> 22:08.953
[Danny continues whispering indistinctly]

22:12.999 --> 22:15.376
[laughs] Thanks for the tip.

22:15.585 --> 22:18.588
[in normal voice]
Took me 45 years to figure that out.

22:19.089 --> 22:20.131
Good night, Mom.

22:20.339 --> 22:22.008
Good night, honey.

22:29.473 --> 22:31.768
You want me to get rid of this guy?

22:33.352 --> 22:36.689
[both chuckle]

22:39.442 --> 22:40.526
What'd you say to her?

22:41.485 --> 22:43.780
Oh, that's between
an uncle and his niece.

22:44.155 --> 22:47.117
- What?
- I said, that's between an uncle

22:47.200 --> 22:48.618
and his niece.

23:04.467 --> 23:07.304
Every time that kid leaves,
it puts a pit in my stomach.

23:08.638 --> 23:10.056
She's always gonna come home.

23:10.140 --> 23:13.601
I mean, look what she's got
to come back to. Heh.

23:14.894 --> 23:17.272
How the fuck did it not
destroy Mom and Dad?

23:21.901 --> 23:25.404
Anything ever happened to one of my kids,
I don't know what the fuck I'd do.

23:29.617 --> 23:32.578
Yeah, you worry too much. You're a cop.

23:32.787 --> 23:35.832
You got the safest kids
in the whole town.

23:42.755 --> 23:44.757
[♪♪♪]

24:32.305 --> 24:34.307
That was nice, right?

24:35.516 --> 24:37.977
Yeah, it was.

24:40.855 --> 24:42.440
What are you thinking?

24:46.277 --> 24:47.862
Nothing.

24:48.654 --> 24:50.948
I'm just glad you're happy.

24:58.164 --> 25:01.000
The only thing the prosecution
has is an unreliable witness

25:01.084 --> 25:03.878
who happens to be dating
your accuser's sister.

25:04.087 --> 25:06.881
All I was trying to do was
get my money back from this guy.

25:07.090 --> 25:08.966
I know.

25:10.301 --> 25:12.845
You know, I-- I know the prosecutor.

25:13.054 --> 25:14.597
She's reasonable.

25:14.805 --> 25:17.016
I think I can get her
to reduce your charges.

25:17.225 --> 25:19.060
I'm grateful, Miss Rayburn.

25:19.269 --> 25:20.561
Very grateful. Thank you.

25:22.521 --> 25:25.400
And what does this mean for my bail?
Am I still on the hook?

25:25.608 --> 25:28.486
Until your case clears, yes.
Unfortunately.

25:33.324 --> 25:36.160
- Mrs. Rayburn.
- Oh, hey, Carlos.

25:36.369 --> 25:39.538
Good to see you.
Oh, no. Please, sit down.

25:40.081 --> 25:41.874
I hope I'm not a distraction.

25:42.083 --> 25:44.461
Especially after Robert's passing.
So sorry to hear.

25:45.544 --> 25:47.213
Thank you.

25:47.422 --> 25:50.133
Meg told me about your case.

25:50.341 --> 25:52.969
My mother wants to sign
a character affidavit.

25:53.177 --> 25:54.804
I think it could really help us.

25:55.012 --> 25:57.014
No, Mrs. Rayburn.
You don't have to do that.

25:57.223 --> 25:59.725
We all make mistakes.

26:00.518 --> 26:03.354
Oh. Where are you staying?

26:03.980 --> 26:05.773
With Manny and his folks.

26:05.982 --> 26:08.234
They got me sober. Saved my life.

26:08.443 --> 26:10.194
Well, that's what family's for, right?

26:10.403 --> 26:12.280
Not all families would do that.

26:12.489 --> 26:14.573
- I'm very lucky.
- You are.

26:14.782 --> 26:17.118
Good to see you, Carlos.

26:22.206 --> 26:24.167
[Nick]
Rayburn!

26:25.876 --> 26:27.795
You went behind my back.

26:28.338 --> 26:30.548
That was some deal
you conned my mother into.

26:30.756 --> 26:32.591
Whoa, I'm paying your mother
a lot of money.

26:32.800 --> 26:34.802
It's nowhere near the amount I secured.

26:35.011 --> 26:38.348
Listen, your mom is no dummy.
She wants to keep this place pristine.

26:38.556 --> 26:40.475
Spare me the sanctimonious bullshit.

26:40.683 --> 26:43.853
They were gonna dredge this inlet
to make room for those 50-footers.

26:44.061 --> 26:46.564
Your mom made a sacrifice.
She's doing the right thing.

26:46.772 --> 26:48.483
This land is all she's got.

26:49.025 --> 26:52.487
Well, I guess she didn't want her legacy
to be another fucking yacht club.

26:52.695 --> 26:55.365
Or she didn't feel great about
putting me out of business.

26:55.573 --> 26:57.283
You're a piece of shit, Rayburn.

26:57.825 --> 27:00.328
I can't help it if your mom
likes me better than you.

27:00.411 --> 27:01.454
Fuck you.

27:03.540 --> 27:05.416
You better hope you don't get that loan.

27:24.143 --> 27:26.145
How you doing, man?

27:29.440 --> 27:32.318
- Oh, I'm fine.
- Good.

27:39.450 --> 27:41.660
How's my sister doing?

27:44.330 --> 27:46.290
I really don't know.

27:46.874 --> 27:49.210
I mean, she's been really restless lately.

27:51.670 --> 27:53.839
But when your dad passed away,

27:54.048 --> 27:56.759
all of a sudden, overnight, boom.
She wants to get married.

27:56.967 --> 27:58.261
Really?

28:04.808 --> 28:07.395
I don't understand women.

28:08.605 --> 28:11.732
And I sure as hell
don't understand my sister.

28:28.791 --> 28:30.793
[inaudible dialogue]

28:40.052 --> 28:41.762
[Meg] I'll let you know what I hear.

28:41.845 --> 28:44.848
[Carlos] Sure. Thank you very much.
Talk to you soon.

28:50.980 --> 28:53.732
- Hey, man. How are you doing? Good?
- [Carlos] Good morning.

28:54.275 --> 28:57.278
- Hey, mister.
- [Meg] Hey, you. How you doing?

28:57.487 --> 29:00.323
Good. Yeah, I'm good.

29:00.948 --> 29:04.785
- Who was that?
- Carlos Mejia. You remember him?

29:04.994 --> 29:07.997
- Oh, Manny's, what, brother?
- Cousin.

29:08.205 --> 29:09.582
Yeah, the drunk.

29:09.790 --> 29:12.585
Shut up. That is harsh.

29:13.711 --> 29:16.213
- Didn't Dad fire him?
- Yes. A few years ago.

29:16.380 --> 29:18.299
But he's-- I don't know,
he's had it tough,

29:18.466 --> 29:20.176
so he's getting sober now.

29:20.718 --> 29:22.094
- Oh, yeah?
- Mm-hm.

29:22.261 --> 29:24.930
Well, good for him. Good for him.
Does he work for us now?

29:25.097 --> 29:28.392
No. No. He just...

29:28.601 --> 29:31.270
He has some legal troubles,
so I'm just helping him out.

29:31.812 --> 29:34.524
No, I saw Mom
handing him an envelope.

29:34.898 --> 29:37.818
Oh. He put his mom's house up for bail.

29:37.985 --> 29:40.946
So we're just pitching in
until he gets up on his feet.

29:41.155 --> 29:43.115
- That's good. That's good.
- Mm-hm.

29:43.324 --> 29:46.118
It's good when the family
can help other people out.

29:47.370 --> 29:49.580
I mean, because, it's why people...

29:50.331 --> 29:51.874
They love working for us, right?

29:52.916 --> 29:55.753
It's loyalty.

29:56.754 --> 29:59.423
[indistinct chatter in Spanish]

30:17.692 --> 30:19.694
[speaking indistinctly]

30:20.695 --> 30:23.239
- [John] Mr. Bezler?
- Good afternoon, gentlemen.

30:23.322 --> 30:25.949
Detective Diaz, Detective Rayburn.

30:26.158 --> 30:28.118
[Marco]
Beautiful land. You own this place?

30:28.327 --> 30:30.162
It's been in the family for generations.

30:30.871 --> 30:33.040
Seventy-two, '73?

30:33.916 --> 30:37.878
- [Bezler] 1970. First truck I ever owned.
- [Marco] Beautiful.

30:38.087 --> 30:41.006
My grandfather had
a baby blue '66 C10 with whitewalls.

30:41.215 --> 30:42.633
He called her Camilla. He loved her.

30:42.717 --> 30:45.219
[laughs]
Why don't you take a look inside?

30:45.428 --> 30:47.346
- You got more of this?
- Oh, yeah.

30:51.684 --> 30:53.561
[Marco]
Seventy-five Caprice Classic?

30:54.478 --> 30:56.105
1946 Chevrolet.

30:56.313 --> 30:58.107
As knowledgeable
as you are, detective,

30:58.274 --> 31:01.778
I'm sure you didn't drive out here
to discuss the virtues of the automobile.

31:01.985 --> 31:04.572
No. We came here
to talk to your employees.

31:05.281 --> 31:07.700
[laughs]
I'm afraid that just isn't possible.

31:07.866 --> 31:09.159
Well, why is that?

31:09.326 --> 31:10.745
This is private property.

31:10.828 --> 31:13.456
If you don't have a warrant,
I'm gonna ask you to leave.

31:13.623 --> 31:16.333
Sorry. We're not here
to investigate your hiring practices.

31:16.500 --> 31:19.837
- We can get a search warrant if you want.
- Yeah, not a problem.

31:20.379 --> 31:23.299
If we do that, might as well
invite all the guys here too.

31:23.507 --> 31:26.135
Yeah, he plays softball
with some guys from INS.

31:26.719 --> 31:29.221
Can't hit for shit,
but they are sticklers for detail--

31:29.305 --> 31:32.391
Maybe that wouldn't be a good idea.
They're gonna seize your books

31:32.475 --> 31:34.393
and scour through
your employment records.

31:34.602 --> 31:37.104
All of my employees
provide paperwork.

31:37.313 --> 31:40.357
Oh, I'm sure they do.
And I'm sure some of it's even legit.

31:40.566 --> 31:42.067
John, you know, I envy your guys.

31:42.276 --> 31:46.155
They're gonna come here and
they're gonna have a fucking field day.

31:46.572 --> 31:48.115
[John]
Tell you what I'm gonna do.

31:49.032 --> 31:51.910
I'm gonna let you make the decision.

31:52.161 --> 31:54.163
[Marco speaking in Spanish]

31:55.539 --> 31:57.541
[♪♪♪]

32:32.910 --> 32:35.538
[Marco continues speaking in Spanish]

33:04.692 --> 33:06.068
What does that say?

33:08.070 --> 33:09.488
[Marco reads note]

33:09.572 --> 33:11.532
[Marco]
"The good neighbor."

33:11.990 --> 33:13.743
What does this mean?

33:21.208 --> 33:23.920
I think it means
someone's trying to help us.

33:28.591 --> 33:30.927
[Kevin]
No, we'll get it done by 8.

33:31.385 --> 33:32.803
Okay, thanks a lot.

33:33.011 --> 33:34.513
- Hey.
- Hi.

33:34.722 --> 33:37.015
- Just came from the bank.
- Yeah? How's it look?

33:37.224 --> 33:39.476
Property's been assessed.
Everything is in order.

33:39.685 --> 33:43.230
You have to be sure Belle doesn't file
for divorce before that comes through.

33:43.439 --> 33:45.441
- Okay.
- She could torpedo the whole thing.

33:45.649 --> 33:48.861
- Okay. Hey, thanks for doing this.
- Yeah.

33:49.027 --> 33:51.447
I actually wouldn't advise you
going through with it,

33:51.614 --> 33:53.490
but you're so determined.

33:53.699 --> 33:55.367
It's a lot of money, I know, I know.

33:55.576 --> 33:58.996
But, frankly, I don't have another option.

33:59.204 --> 34:01.498
I'm barely keeping
my head above water here.

34:01.707 --> 34:03.000
So you take on debt?

34:03.208 --> 34:06.754
Listen, if I get the property,
I can expand, you know?

34:06.963 --> 34:08.422
I'll-- I'll pay it back.

34:08.631 --> 34:10.883
Well, you better.
Or they're gonna own the place.

34:11.091 --> 34:12.802
I know how it works, Meg. Okay?

34:13.010 --> 34:14.470
All right.

34:16.054 --> 34:18.808
Hey, did you think about
that other thing?

34:19.016 --> 34:20.643
Cutting Danny back in?

34:21.727 --> 34:23.479
Did you?

34:24.021 --> 34:26.231
I just want us all
to be on the same page.

34:29.151 --> 34:31.111
Well, I don't wanna
stand in anybody's way.

34:31.320 --> 34:34.197
If it's okay with you guys,
it's okay with me.

34:37.618 --> 34:39.662
- You're sure?
- Yeah.

34:39.870 --> 34:42.706
I mean, you know,
he's made mistakes, but--

34:42.915 --> 34:45.542
I mean, we've all done things
we're not proud of.

34:46.836 --> 34:48.671
But listen, maybe it's all for the best.

34:48.879 --> 34:51.841
He'll feel included.
He won't flake out again.

34:54.468 --> 34:56.136
All right. Good.

34:56.345 --> 34:58.681
I will draw up all the paperwork.

34:59.723 --> 35:01.308
- Thank you.
- I'll see you later?

35:01.517 --> 35:03.602
- Yeah. Thank you.
- Of course.

35:13.320 --> 35:16.073
[Kevin]
Look at all of this shit.

35:19.910 --> 35:24.122
My God, I have not seen the inside
of Dad's shed since I was a little kid.

35:24.623 --> 35:26.959
The man was very particular
about who he let in.

35:27.043 --> 35:28.126
[Kevin chuckles]

35:29.545 --> 35:32.048
- You want something?
- Yeah, actually... Uh...

35:32.255 --> 35:35.342
I've been meaning to
talk to you about something, uh...

35:37.135 --> 35:41.015
The other night, I kind of hooked up with
somebody that I probably shouldn't have.

35:41.223 --> 35:44.101
Hm. Why are you telling me?

35:44.309 --> 35:46.520
Uh, it was Chelsea.

35:48.564 --> 35:50.566
Yeah, I saw her at this bar.

35:50.774 --> 35:54.194
I was out of my mind.
She was wasted.

35:54.403 --> 35:56.072
It was just so stupid.

35:56.279 --> 35:58.949
And one thing led to another. It was...

35:59.909 --> 36:01.410
It was a total dickhead move

36:01.618 --> 36:06.248
and if you're pissed off,
I completely understand.

36:08.751 --> 36:10.377
Because it just dawned on me later,

36:10.586 --> 36:14.214
maybe that you guys had
sort of something going on.

36:14.423 --> 36:18.135
- In which case, Danny-- Okay.
- Kevin, I said it's fine.

36:21.638 --> 36:25.308
I don't think I said anything,
but Belle and I are breaking up.

36:26.351 --> 36:27.937
- Shit.
- Yep.

36:28.145 --> 36:31.690
Headed for the big D.
Got a lawyer and everything.

36:33.776 --> 36:36.653
It's been a--
It's been a pretty rough time.

36:38.196 --> 36:42.242
And now I'm this age
and I am single again.

36:42.451 --> 36:45.871
It's... It's a horrible feeling.

36:46.413 --> 36:48.415
Yeah. Yeah, I bet.

36:48.624 --> 36:50.167
It's the worst.

36:53.837 --> 36:55.798
So no hard feelings? We're good?

36:58.300 --> 37:00.136
- No hard feelings.
- Yeah?

37:02.179 --> 37:05.515
Okay. Thanks.

37:13.607 --> 37:15.275
All right.

37:17.194 --> 37:18.445
See you, man.

37:36.172 --> 37:37.881
Your sister home?

37:38.090 --> 37:39.925
She's at work.

37:40.134 --> 37:43.095
Why aren't you dressed, man?
We got work to do.

37:43.303 --> 37:45.263
The jig is up, dude. It's over.

37:45.472 --> 37:46.807
What?

37:47.975 --> 37:51.394
Don't shoot the messenger, okay?

37:53.022 --> 37:54.690
They're done with us.

37:54.898 --> 37:57.193
Word is, the docks are hot.

37:57.400 --> 37:59.987
- Which dock?
- Tom's Harbor? I don't know.

38:00.196 --> 38:03.115
Whatever fucking docks
they unload their shit at.

38:03.323 --> 38:07.536
Cops have been sniffing around,
they wanna shut us down for a while.

38:07.744 --> 38:09.788
Hey, you gotta introduce me
to these guys.

38:09.997 --> 38:13.375
- You gotta let me talk to them.
- I'm not fucking currently suicidal.

38:13.583 --> 38:15.377
- No fucking way.
- I need the money.

38:15.585 --> 38:18.088
- Eric, I need the money.
- I know!

38:18.922 --> 38:20.883
- I need the money.
- I know.

38:21.091 --> 38:24.761
I don't know what to tell you, bro.
I'm getting the rest of the dough tonight.

38:24.970 --> 38:28.057
- When?
- I'll get your cut by midnight.

38:28.265 --> 38:31.852
Tonight, I'm meeting the guy
and I'll get it to you.

38:33.562 --> 38:35.272
It's fucking bullshit.

38:35.480 --> 38:37.066
- It's bullshit.
- Yeah.

38:37.149 --> 38:38.901
[engine starts]

38:38.984 --> 38:40.694
I gotta go.

38:53.040 --> 38:55.042
[organ playing]

39:06.136 --> 39:08.138
[speaking indistinctly]

39:09.806 --> 39:11.892
Excuse me. Excuse me.

39:12.101 --> 39:14.811
- I'm sorry.
- May I help you?

39:14.937 --> 39:17.647
I'm with the sheriff's office.
Wondering if you can help.

39:17.731 --> 39:20.067
I'm trying to get some
information on these girls.

39:25.572 --> 39:27.407
They weren't members
of my congregation.

39:28.784 --> 39:31.745
I was directed to this church,
specifically.

39:31.954 --> 39:33.371
By who?

39:33.580 --> 39:36.250
Well, unfortunately
it was an anonymous tip.

39:36.792 --> 39:39.295
Hey, look. I'm not trying
to look for any trouble here.

39:39.502 --> 39:43.006
I'm trying to get information on
these girls and that's it. I promise you.

39:44.258 --> 39:46.384
Take one more look.

39:48.428 --> 39:51.848
- I'm sorry.
- If by any chance...

39:52.308 --> 39:55.185
- Could you give me a call?
- All right.

39:55.393 --> 39:57.146
Thank you for your time.

40:09.825 --> 40:11.327
[scoffs]

40:15.747 --> 40:17.749
[♪♪♪]

40:54.286 --> 40:55.704
[truck door closes]

42:13.573 --> 42:15.284
[door beeps]

42:16.201 --> 42:18.203
[indistinct chattering]

42:22.916 --> 42:25.668
Something else. There was black--
He could've gone like a--

42:26.211 --> 42:27.921
The fuck! Yo!

42:28.130 --> 42:30.882
- What the fuck are you doing?
- Chill, chill. I wanna talk.

42:31.049 --> 42:34.470
- Just wanna talk to whoever's in charge.
- Shut the fuck up and sit down.

42:41.184 --> 42:43.061
You in charge?

42:44.813 --> 42:47.149
Or just the asshole with a gun?

42:47.357 --> 42:48.942
You in charge?

42:49.151 --> 42:51.903
You just-- Who's in charge?

42:54.323 --> 42:55.949
[toilet flushing]

42:57.742 --> 43:00.370
You got a lot of questions.

43:03.457 --> 43:08.128
A man can't even take a shit
without some stranger walking in. Heh.

43:09.004 --> 43:11.381
So, who the fuck are you?

43:13.091 --> 43:15.344
- I work for you.
- No, you don't.

43:15.552 --> 43:19.097
I run a little bait shop.
Sell fishing poles.

43:19.306 --> 43:22.058
I only got a few employees,
and you ain't one of them.

43:22.934 --> 43:25.687
So let's take this again.

43:26.604 --> 43:29.065
Who the fuck are you?

43:30.775 --> 43:34.279
I deliver gas cans out to the mangroves.

43:34.488 --> 43:36.532
Lately, that line of work has dried up

43:36.739 --> 43:40.076
and I hear you may be
catching some heat.

43:41.328 --> 43:43.746
And how is that any of your business?

43:45.499 --> 43:49.503
Well, I might be able to help you out.

43:50.086 --> 43:53.215
I might be able
to solve the problem for you.

43:56.593 --> 43:58.512
Hey, look, I'm only trying to help, okay?

43:58.720 --> 44:02.474
You wanna ask this guy
to lower the gun, and I can talk to you?

44:12.901 --> 44:15.904
I guess you really don't know who I am.

44:38.760 --> 44:40.803
It's fucking late, you know that?

44:43.306 --> 44:46.602
Is it too late for me to apologize to you?

44:47.185 --> 44:50.939
I was... such an asshole.

44:53.650 --> 44:55.485
Yeah, you were.

44:56.152 --> 44:57.779
A really big fucking asshole.

44:57.987 --> 45:00.990
And I don't wanna be that. Not to you.

45:03.243 --> 45:04.786
Then don't.

45:08.457 --> 45:11.209
I know about you and my brother.

45:12.461 --> 45:14.463
[♪♪♪]

45:25.641 --> 45:28.059
Yeah, it was fucking stupid,
but it happened, so...

45:29.352 --> 45:31.104
It's okay. It's okay.

45:31.271 --> 45:33.523
It's not like you have a right
to tell me who I can be with.

45:33.690 --> 45:36.359
No. No, I don't.

45:47.078 --> 45:52.375
Sometimes... things happen...

45:53.293 --> 45:56.254
and you get clear in your mind.

45:57.673 --> 46:00.091
You know who you are.

46:00.425 --> 46:02.969
You know what you want.

46:03.470 --> 46:07.223
And you know what you have to do.

46:08.684 --> 46:10.935
[grunting and groaning]

46:26.326 --> 46:30.246
So I'm gonna be around for a while.

46:30.747 --> 46:33.875
If you decide you can forgive me,
I'd love it if you'd call.

46:33.958 --> 46:35.251
[Kevin exclaims]

46:35.418 --> 46:37.587
[groans then grunts]

46:37.795 --> 46:39.506
Hey.

46:42.425 --> 46:45.053
You and your brother...

46:47.430 --> 46:50.141
you're the closest thing I got to family.

46:50.350 --> 46:51.893
[♪♪♪]

47:11.413 --> 47:13.415
[static crackling]

47:15.291 --> 47:18.127
[Potts on recording]
All you have to do is tell me the truth.

47:18.878 --> 47:21.130
Let's start with your name.

47:22.340 --> 47:26.386
I'm Kevin. Kevin Rayburn.

47:27.970 --> 47:30.056
[Potts]
And you were there.

47:31.767 --> 47:34.436
You saw the car hit your brother?

47:36.979 --> 47:38.774
Yes, sir.

47:39.190 --> 47:41.401
Danny was screaming and crying.

47:42.485 --> 47:44.487
[♪♪♪]

47:47.282 --> 47:50.201
I never saw someone get hurt that bad.

47:58.209 --> 48:00.211
[♪♪♪]

48:05.717 --> 48:07.719
[upbeat country music plays]
